19QualifiedName QualifiedName::Parse(std::string qualified_name) {
20 std::vector<std::string> qualifications;
21 while (true) {
22 size_t namespace_delimiter_index = qualified_name.find("::");
23 if (namespace_delimiter_index == std::string::npos) break;
24 qualifications.push_back(
25 qualified_name.substr(0, namespace_delimiter_index));
26 qualified_name = qualified_name.substr(namespace_delimiter_index + 2);
27 }
28 return QualifiedName(qualifications, qualified_name);
29}

31std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const QualifiedName& name) {
32 for (const std::string& qualifier : name.namespace_qualification) {
33 os << qualifier << "::";
34 }
35 return os << name.name;
36}

38std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const Callable& m) {
39 os << "callable " << m.ReadableName() << "(";
40 if (m.signature().implicit_count != 0) {
41 os << "implicit ";
42 TypeVector implicit_parameter_types(
43 m.signature().parameter_types.types.begin(),
44 m.signature().parameter_types.types.begin() +
45 m.signature().implicit_count);
46 os << implicit_parameter_types << ")(";
47 TypeVector explicit_parameter_types(
48 m.signature().parameter_types.types.begin() +
49 m.signature().implicit_count,
50 m.signature().parameter_types.types.end());
51 os << explicit_parameter_types;
52 } else {
53 os << m.signature().parameter_types;
54 }
55 os << "): " << *m.signature().return_type;
56 return os;
57}

71std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const GenericCallable& g) {
72 os << "generic " << g.name() << "<";
73 PrintCommaSeparatedList(os, g.generic_parameters(),
74 [](const GenericParameter& identifier) {

82SpecializationRequester::SpecializationRequester(SourcePosition position,
83 Scope* s, std::string name)
84 : position(position), name(std::move(name)) {
85 // Skip scopes that are not related to template specializations, they might be
86 // stack-allocated and not live for long enough.
87 while (s && s->GetSpecializationRequester().IsNone()) s = s->ParentScope();
88 this->scope = s;
89}

91std::vector<Declarable*> Scope::Lookup(const QualifiedName& name) {
92 if (!name.namespace_qualification.empty() &&
93 name.namespace_qualification[0].empty()) {
94 return GlobalContext::GetDefaultNamespace()->Lookup(
95 name.DropFirstNamespaceQualification());
96 }
97 std::vector<Declarable*> result;
98 if (ParentScope()) {
99 result = ParentScope()->Lookup(name);
100 }
101 for (Declarable* declarable : LookupShallow(name)) {
102 result.push_back(declarable);
103 }
104 return result;
105}

107base::Optional<std::string> TypeConstraint::IsViolated(const Type* type) const {
108 if (upper_bound && !type->IsSubtypeOf(*upper_bound)) {
109 if (type->IsTopType()) {
110 return TopType::cast(type)->reason();
111 } else {
112 return {
113 ToString("expected ", *type, " to be a subtype of ", **upper_bound)};
114 }
115 }
116 return base::nullopt;
117}
118
119base::Optional<std::string> FindConstraintViolation(
120 const std::vector<const Type*>& types,
121 const std::vector<TypeConstraint>& constraints) {
122 DCHECK_EQ(constraints.size(), types.size());
123 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); ++i) {
124 if (auto violation = constraints[i].IsViolated(types[i])) {
125 return {"Could not instantiate generic, " + *violation + "."};
126 }
127 }
128 return base::nullopt;
129}
130
131std::vector<TypeConstraint> ComputeConstraints(
132 Scope* scope, const GenericParameters& parameters) {
133 CurrentScope::Scope scope_scope(scope);
134 std::vector<TypeConstraint> result;
135 for (const GenericParameter& parameter : parameters) {
136 if (parameter.constraint) {
137 result.push_back(TypeConstraint::SubtypeConstraint(
138 TypeVisitor::ComputeType(*parameter.constraint)));
139 } else {
140 result.push_back(TypeConstraint::Unconstrained());
141 }
142 }
143 return result;
144}
145
146TypeArgumentInference GenericCallable::InferSpecializationTypes(
147 const TypeVector& explicit_specialization_types,
148 const std::vector<base::Optional<const Type*>>& arguments) {
149 const std::vector<TypeExpression*>& parameters =
150 declaration()->parameters.types;
151 CurrentScope::Scope generic_scope(ParentScope());
152 TypeArgumentInference inference(generic_parameters(),
153 explicit_specialization_types, parameters,
154 arguments);
155 if (!inference.HasFailed()) {
156 if (auto violation =
157 FindConstraintViolation(inference.GetResult(), Constraints())) {
158 inference.Fail(*violation);
159 }
160 }
161 return inference;
162}

164base::Optional<Statement*> GenericCallable::CallableBody() {
165 if (auto* macro_decl = TorqueMacroDeclaration::DynamicCast(declaration())) {
166 return macro_decl->body;
167 } else if (auto* builtin_decl =
168 TorqueBuiltinDeclaration::DynamicCast(declaration())) {
169 return builtin_decl->body;
170 } else {
171 return base::nullopt;
172 }
173}

181const Type* TypeAlias::Resolve() const {
182 if (!type_) {
183 CurrentScope::Scope scope_activator(ParentScope());
184 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope position_activator(Position());
185 TypeDeclaration* decl = *delayed_;
186 if (being_resolved_) {
187 std::stringstream s;
188 s << "Cannot create type " << decl->name->value
189 << " due to circular dependencies.";
190 ReportError(s.str());
191 }
192 type_ = TypeVisitor::ComputeType(decl);
193 }
194 return *type_;
195}
